# Frontend replication (web and mobile)

This project has **two separate frontend codebases**: `apps/web` (desktop + mobile web) and `apps/mobile` (Capacitor for iOS/Android). There are no shared packages; each app has its own types, API client, and components.

**Rule:** When adding or changing UI or features in `apps/web`, replicate the same UI and behavior in `apps/mobile`. When adding or changing UI or features in `apps/mobile`, replicate the same in `apps/web`. Keep screens, components, and feature behavior in sync across both apps.

**What to replicate:**
- New or updated screens and page components
- New or updated shared components (buttons, cards, forms, layout)
- New or updated flows (e.g. auth, check-in, groups)
- Route structure and navigation (use the same route names and params, e.g. `/places/:placeCode`, `/groups/:groupCode`)
- Design tokens and Tailwind theme usage

**What may differ:**
- App-specific config (e.g. Capacitor plugins, native env, build config)
- Environment variable names or loading (e.g. `VITE_API_URL` in each app)
- Deployment or run scripts

After editing one app, update the other so both stay in sync.
